channel.description:
[center][size=32pt]Game Level (Map) Editor - Version 1[/size]
[size=28pt]by: Davidi2[/size][/center]

I am creating a game similar to the first Mario Bros games. The ones where you avoid the barrels and try to reach the top of the level by climbing ladders etc. Before I even started making the game, I decided that I should allow people to make their own maps for the game, other then the normal ones that it would come with. I was going to release the game and the level editor at the same time, but the game is taking me longer than expected and I'm not sure the codes all put together would be less then 20,000 characters. 

So let me start explaining the program.
You start out with a blank black slate, and a Control Panel with some options on it. The levels are 33x33 grid based, and each grid space (I will use the term tile) can be taken up by almost any tile in the Control Panel. The tiles are:

[ul][li]Block - Walkable tile[/li]
[li]Water - Not walkable, kills on contact from top or sides[/li]
[li]Ladder - Climbable and walkable[/li]
[li]Spike - Not walkable, kills on contact from top[/li]
[li]Blank - Not walkable, player falls when in contact[/li]
[li]Player start - Represents the player start position[/li][/ul]


Just to understand more, you beat the level when you reach the door, which has yet to be added. I'm still deciding how that part will work with the game, so I haven't put it in yet.

[b]For MoparScapers: You place tiles by selecting the corresponding tile in the Control Panel, and clicking/dragging the mouse over the area you want the tile added.[/b]

Some more information:

[ul][li]The tiles are images in the format [b]M[/b]ap[b]E[/b]ditor[b]I[/b]mage, a custom file extension for this application. (*.mei)[/li]
[li]This application also supporst saving and loading, map backup, and corrupt file detection. The saved  [b]M[/b]ap[b]E[/b]ditor[b]M[/b]apdata, a custom file extension for this application. (*.mem)[/li]
[li]You can shrink the Control Panel by pressing hide, or clicking the exit button on it. The Control Panel will not close until the main panel closes however.[/li][/ul]


Now here is the source code:

First class - Extends File Filter - MainFilter.java
[b]Used for saving and loading maps with a JDialog[/b]
[code]import java.io.*;

public class MainFilter extends javax.swing.filechooser.FileFilter {
	public boolean accept(File chosen) {
		if(chosen.isDirectory())
			return true;
		String fileName = chosen.getName();
		if(fileName.matches(".*(.mem)")) {
			return true;
		}
		else
			return false;
	}

	public String getDescription() {
		return "Maps (*.mem)";
	}
}
[/code]

Second class - Extends JFrame - MainFrame.java
[b]The main panel. This is where the map is shown. You must also close this to close the Control Panel and stop the program[/b]
[code]import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.geom.*;
import javax.swing.*;
import javax.swing.event.*; 
import java.awt.event.*;

public class MainFrame extends JFrame {

	public ImageIcon ladder;
	public ImageIcon block;
	public ImageIcon blank;
	public ImageIcon water;
	public ImageIcon spike;
	public ImageIcon playerStart;
	JPanel panel1 = new JPanel();
	int[][] grid = new int[33][33];
	JLabel[][] gridL = new JLabel[33][33];
	public boolean overwrite = true;
	public int tileID = 0;
	public boolean playerStartActive = false;

	public MainFrame() {
		ladder = new ImageIcon("Data/1.mei");
		block = new ImageIcon("Data/2.mei");
		blank = new ImageIcon("Data/3.mei");
		water = new ImageIcon("Data/4.mei");
		spike = new ImageIcon("Data/5.mei");
		playerStart = new ImageIcon("Data/6.mei");
		initializeComponent();
		this.setVisible(true);
	}

	public static void main(String args[]) {
		MainFrame main = new MainFrame();
		SecondFrame second = new SecondFrame(main);
	}

	public String getRowStringRepresentation(int row) {
		String currentString = "";
		for(int i = 0; i < 33; i++) {
			currentString += grid[i][row];
		}
		return currentString;
	}

	public void addTile(int xSpot, int ySpot, int id) {
		if(gridL[xSpot][ySpot] != null && grid[xSpot][ySpot] != 2 && !overwrite && id != 2) {
			return;
		}
		if(grid[xSpot][ySpot] == 5 && id != 5) {
			playerStartActive = false;
		}
		if(id == 5 && grid[xSpot][ySpot] != 5 && playerStartActive) {
			JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "You are attempting to add a player start when one already exists on the field!\nPlease erase the old one first!", "Warning", JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);
			return;
		}
		if(gridL[xSpot][ySpot] != null) {
			panel1.remove(gridL[xSpot][ySpot]);
		}
		grid[xSpot][ySpot] = id;
		switch (id) {
			case 0:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(ladder);
			break;
			case 1:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(block);
			break;
			case 2:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(blank);
			break;
			case 3:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(water);
			break;
			case 4:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(spike);
			break;
			case 5:
				gridL[xSpot][ySpot] = new JLabel(playerStart);
				playerStartActive = true;
			break;
		}
		gridL[xSpot][ySpot].setBounds(xSpot*20, ySpot*20, 20, 20);
		panel1.add(gridL[xSpot][ySpot]);	
		panel1.repaint();
	}

	private void initializeComponent() {
		panel1.setLayout(null);

		this.add(panel1);
		for(int y = 0; y < 33; y++) {
			for(int x = 0; x < 33; x++) {
				addTile(x, y, 2);
			}
		}
		panel1.repaint();
		this.add(panel1);
		this.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
		this.setSize(663,685);
		this.setLocation(50,25);
		this.setVisible(true);
		this.setTitle("Map Editor");
		this.setResizable(false);
        	this.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter() {
 			public void mouseReleased(MouseEvent e) { 
				int xSpot = (int)((e.getX()-3)/20);
				int ySpot = (int)((e.getY()-25)/20);
				if(xSpot > -1 && ySpot > -1 && xSpot < 33 && ySpot < 33) {
					addTile(xSpot, ySpot, tileID);
				}
 			} 
  		}); 
        	this.addMouseMotionListener(new MouseMotionAdapter() {
 			public void mouseDragged(MouseEvent e) { 
				int xSpot = (int)((e.getX()-3)/20);
				int ySpot = (int)((e.getY()-25)/20);
				if(xSpot > -1 && ySpot > -1 && xSpot < 33 && ySpot < 33) {
					addTile(xSpot, ySpot, tileID);
				}
			} 
  		}); 
	}

}
[/code]

Third class - Extends JDialog - SecondFrame.java
[b]The control panel. This is where you select tiles and save/load maps. Note this panel cannot be closed without closing the main panel.[/b]
[code]import java.awt.*;
import javax.swing.*;
import javax.swing.event.*; 
import java.awt.event.*;
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class SecondFrame extends JDialog implements ActionListener {

	ImageIcon ladder;
	ImageIcon block;
	ImageIcon blank;
	ImageIcon water;
	ImageIcon spike;
	ImageIcon playerStart;
	MainFrame mf;
	JLabel dir1;
	JButton ladderButton;
	JButton playerButton;
	JButton blockButton;
	JButton blankButton;
	JButton waterButton;
	JButton spikeButton;
	JButton saveButton;
	JButton openButton;
	JButton showButton;
	JButton hideButton;
	JPanel panel1 = new JPanel();
	JLabel currentTile = new JLabel("Selected Tile: ladder");
	JCheckBox overwrite;
	ArrayList<String> readLines = new ArrayList<String>();

	public SecondFrame(MainFrame mf) {
		ladder = mf.ladder;
		block = mf.block;
		blank = mf.blank;
		water = mf.water;
		spike = mf.spike;
		this.mf = mf;
		this.playerStart = mf.playerStart;
		initializeComponent();
		this.setVisible(true);
	}

	public void windowClosing(WindowEvent e) {
		this.setSize(20,20);
	}
	public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
		if(e.getSource() == ladderButton) {
			setTile(0);
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == blockButton) {
			setTile(1);
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == blankButton) {
			setTile(2);
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == waterButton) {
			setTile(3);
		}	
		else if(e.getSource() == spikeButton) {
			setTile(4);
		}		
		else if(e.getSource() == overwrite) {
			setOverwrite();
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == showButton) {
			tempShow();
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == hideButton) {
			tempHide();
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == playerButton) {
			setTile(5);
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == openButton) {
			JFileChooser fc = new JFileChooser();
			fc.addChoosableFileFilter(new MainFilter());
			fc.setAcceptAllFileFilterUsed(false);
			fc.setMultiSelectionEnabled(false);
			int result = fc.showOpenDialog(null);
			if(result == JFileChooser.APPROVE_OPTION) {
				File f = fc.getSelectedFile();
				loadMap(f);
				return;
			}
		}
		else if(e.getSource() == saveButton) {
			JFileChooser fc = new JFileChooser();
			fc.addChoosableFileFilter(new MainFilter());
			fc.setAcceptAllFileFilterUsed(false);
			int result = fc.showSaveDialog(null);
			if(result == JFileChooser.APPROVE_OPTION) {
				File f = fc.getSelectedFile();
				saveMap(f);
				return;
			}
		}

	}

	public void saveMap(File f) {
		try {
		File finalFile;
		if(f.toString().endsWith(".mem")) {
			finalFile = f;
		}
		else {
			finalFile = new File(f.toString() + ".mem");
		}
		if(finalFile.exists()) {
			JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "You are attempting to overwrite an old file.\nA backup will be kept, and if saving fails the backup will be restored.", "Warning", JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);
			try{
				String line = "";
			BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(finalFile));
			BufferedWriter bbw = new BufferedWriter(new FileWriter("Backup/"+finalFile.getName()));
			line = br.readLine();	
			while(line != null) {
				bbw.write(line);
				bbw.newLine();
				bbw.flush();
				line = br.readLine();
			}
			bbw.close();
			br.close();
		} catch(Exception e) {
				JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Error with backup!\nOverwrite aborted.", "Backup Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
				return;
		}
				if(!finalFile.delete()) {
				JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Error deleting old file for overwrite!\nOverwrite aborted.", "Save Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
				return;
			}
		}
		if(finalFile.createNewFile()) {
			BufferedWriter bw = new BufferedWriter(new FileWriter(finalFile));
			for(int i = 0; i < 33; i++) {	
				String s = mf.getRowStringRepresentation(i);
				bw.write(s);
				bw.newLine();
				bw.flush();
			}
			bw.flush();
			bw.close();
		}
		else {
			JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "There was an error creating the new file!\nYou backup is in the \"Backup\" folder.", "Save Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
			return;
		}	
		} catch(Exception e) { 
			JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "There was a saving error!\n" + e, "Save Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
			return;
		}
	}

		public void loadMap(File f) {
		int counter = 0;
		String line = "";
		try {
			File finalFile;
			if(f.toString().endsWith(".mem")) {
				finalFile = f;
			}
			else {
				JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "That's an invalid file! \nAll maps must be \".mem\"", "File Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
				return;
			}
			BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(finalFile));
			line = br.readLine();	
			while(line != null) {
				String tempString = "";
				for(int x = 0; x < 33; x++) {
					try {
						tempString += line.charAt(x);
						int theInt = Integer.parseInt(tempString);
						tempString = "";
					}
					catch(Exception e) {
						JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "That's a corrupt map file! \nPlease do not edit map files out of the map editor!", "File Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
						br.close();
						return;
					}
				}
				readLines.add(line);
				if(line.length() != 33) {
					JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "That's a corrupt map file! \nPlease do not edit map files out of the map editor!", "File Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
					br.close();
					return;
				}
				counter++;
				line = br.readLine();
			}
			if(counter != 33) {
				JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "That's a corrupt map file! \nPlease do not edit map files out of the map editor!", "File Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
				br.close();
				return;
			}
			writeToMainFrame();
			br.close();		
		} catch(Exception e) {
			JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "That's a corrupt map file! \nPlease do not edit map files out of the map editor!", "File Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
			return;
		}
	}

	public void setOverwrite() {
		if(overwrite.isSelected() == true) {
			mf.overwrite = true;
		}
		else {
			mf.overwrite = false;
		}
	}

	public void writeToMainFrame() {
		mf.overwrite = true;
		int theInt = 0;
		String tempString = "";
		for (int i = 0; i < 33; i++) {
			String s = readLines.get(i);
			for(int x = 0; x < 33; x++) {
				tempString += s.charAt(x);
				theInt = Integer.parseInt(tempString);
				mf.addTile(x, i, theInt);
				tempString = "";
			}
		}
		setOverwrite();
	}
	public void setTile(int id) {
		overwrite.setEnabled(true);
		mf.tileID = id;
		switch(id) {
			case 0:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Ladder");
			break;
			case 1:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Block");
			break;
			case 2:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Eraser");
				overwrite.setSelected(true);
				overwrite.setEnabled(false);
			break;
			case 3:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Water");
			break;
			case 4:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Spike");
			break;			
			case 5:
				currentTile.setText("Selected Tile: Start");
			break;
		}
	}

	public void tempHide() {
		setSize(165,48);
		dir1.setVisible(false);
		showButton.setVisible(true);
	}

	public void tempShow() {
		setSize(165, 190);
		dir1.setVisible(true);
		showButton.setVisible(false);
	}

	private void initializeComponent() {
		hideButton = new JButton("Hide");
		showButton = new JButton("Show");
		saveButton = new JButton("Save");
		openButton = new JButton("Load");
		ladderButton = new JButton(ladder);
		playerButton = new JButton(playerStart);
		spikeButton = new JButton(spike);
		blockButton = new JButton(block);
		blankButton = new JButton(blank);
		waterButton = new JButton(water);
		overwrite = new JCheckBox("Overwrite", true);
		dir1 = new JLabel("Select a tile:");

		openButton.addActionListener(this);
		saveButton.addActionListener(this);
		hideButton.addActionListener(this);
		showButton.addActionListener(this);
		overwrite.addActionListener(this);
		blockButton.addActionListener(this);
		blankButton.addActionListener(this);
		ladderButton.addActionListener(this);
		waterButton.addActionListener(this);
		spikeButton.addActionListener(this);
		playerButton.addActionListener(this);

		showButton.setVisible(false);

		showButton.setToolTipText("Show the control panel");
		hideButton.setToolTipText("Hide the control panel");
		overwrite.setToolTipText("Select to overwrite old tiles when clicking");
		blockButton.setToolTipText("Places a block tile");
		playerButton.setToolTipText("Places a player start position");
		ladderButton.setToolTipText("Places a ladder tile");
		blankButton.setToolTipText("Erases a tile");
		spikeButton.setToolTipText("Places a spike tile");
		waterButton.setToolTipText("Places a water tile");
		saveButton.setToolTipText("Save your map");
		openButton.setToolTipText("Load an existing map");

		panel1.setLayout(null);

		hideButton.setBounds(38, 135, 80, 20);
		showButton.setBounds(38, 1, 80, 20);
		saveButton.setBounds(38, 85, 80, 20);
		openButton.setBounds(38, 110, 80, 20);
		ladderButton.setBounds(5, 20, 20, 20);
		blockButton.setBounds(30, 20, 20, 20);
		blankButton.setBounds(55, 20, 20, 20);
		waterButton.setBounds(80, 20, 20, 20);
		spikeButton.setBounds(105, 20, 20, 20);
		playerButton.setBounds(130, 20, 20, 20);
		dir1.setBounds(5, 2, 100, 15);
		currentTile.setBounds(5, 45, 120, 15);
		overwrite.setBounds(38, 65, 90, 15);

		panel1.add(saveButton);
		panel1.add(openButton);
		panel1.add(ladderButton);
		panel1.add(blockButton);
		panel1.add(spikeButton);
		panel1.add(blankButton);
		panel1.add(waterButton);
		panel1.add(currentTile);
		panel1.add(overwrite);
		panel1.add(playerButton);
		panel1.add(hideButton);
		panel1.add(showButton);
		panel1.add(dir1);

		this.setSize(160, 190);
		this.add(panel1);
		this.setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.DO_NOTHING_ON_CLOSE);
		this.setLocation(650,625);
		this.addWindowListener(new WindowAdapter() {
			boolean minimized = false;
			public void windowClosing(WindowEvent e) {
				minimized = !minimized;
				if(minimized) {
					tempHide();
				}
				else {
					tempShow();
				}
			}
		});
		this.setVisible(true);
		this.setTitle("Control Panel");
		this.setResizable(false);
	}
}

